Reasoning: The paper describes a method that uses machine learning to identify historical travelogues in a large text corpus. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as named entity recognition and topic modeling, which are commonly used in the sub-fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning algorithms (cs.LG) for classification tasks. Finally, the interdisciplinary nature of the research, which combines domain knowledge from the humanities with computational methods, suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
